@terrymanu 

I have checked the repo (https://repository.apache.org/). For legacy version (4.0.0 RC1 ~ 4.0.0), there're Sharding-Proxy's jar. But there's no ShardingSphere-Proxy's jar for new versions yet. 

We have set `<maven.deploy.skip>true</maven.deploy.skip>` for ShardingSphere-Proxy module since 4.1.0. So there're no jar for proxy in 4.1.0/4.1.1 and the following 5.0.0-RC1.

It's very easy to replicate this issue. Just create 2 tables then start up ss-proxy, you will see the error in log right away.

1. Create 2 tables as below:
drop table if exists TEST_01;
CREATE TABLE TEST_01 (
ID varchar(32) DEFAULT NULL
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4;

drop table if exists TEST__1;
CREATE TABLE TEST__1 (
ID1 varchar(32) DEFAULT NULL
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4;

2. Start up ss-proxy, the error will be triggered.

Please let me know if you need any more information. Thanks.

